review 1: Moslem resto with local food and 100% halal.

review 3: I like this food shop a lot. People have great personalities and they know for sure how to cook. So many different tastes i didn't know what to choose i eat every day different things and it was satisfied. address: Jl. Dr. Ir. Soekarno No.77, Dauh Peken, Kec. Tabanan, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 82113, Indonesia
review 1:
This place should be 24/7 Indomart and  Point Cafe... The point Cafe is located inside Indomart.
Restroom and ATM also provided.
Be careful for the traffic, since it is located d in the corner or cross-road @ main road Denpasar - Gilimanuk, a busy inter-province road....
review 2:
Coffee shop that is affiliated with a supermarket. It tries to copy and improve from starbucks as their main idol. The prices are far below what starbucks offers and the coffee are up to par with their idols standard.

Because point is mainly a coffee shop, their other drinks are not as good, but with a supermarket next to it, you'd find a nice variety with far cheaper prices than starbucks
review 3: Enjoyable affordable coffee. This outlet in Indomaret Tabanan. Barista wearing a mask but the uniformed Indomaret staff ignored my request 3 times to wear masks.  Disappointing
review 4: The barista has Good hospitality, nice greetings. Cozy place indoor & outdoor. Also delicious coffee.
review 5: Horror - the owner does not know how to run this business. For her, the ATM BCA is a burden not a sales booster. BCA take the machine .... !!!
